== Overview ==
Essence of '''''Murtlap''''' Tentacles is shown to be a powerfully healing and soothing solution.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
When [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]] serves a detention with [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Dolores Umbridge|Professor Umbridge]], he is required to write lines with [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Torture Quill|a quill which creates a wound on the back of his hand]]. After a week and a half of this, he is in considerable pain. [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hermione Granger|Hermione]] gives him a bowl of Essence of Murtlap Tentacles, which he finds extremely soothing.
When [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Lee Jordan|Lee Jordan]] falls afoul of Professor Umbridge and is similarly abused, Harry recommends Murtlap to him; Lee, then, evidently suggests the same cure to [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Fred and George Weasley|Fred and George]] when they are suffering self-inflicted boils in a rather private place.
It is in ''Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them'' by "Newt Scamander" that we learn that the Murtlap is a rat-like creature with a growth on its back that resembles a sea anemone.
