{{C sharp/Navigation|Keywords|unchecked}}
__TOC__</noinclude>

The {{C sharp|unchecked}} keyword prevents overflow-checking when doing integer arithmetics. It may be used as an ''operator'' on a single expression or as a statement on a whole block of code.

<source lang=CSharp>
int x, y, z;
x = 1222111000;
y = 1222111000;

// used as an operator
z = unchecked(x*y);

// used as a statement
unchecked {
  z = x*y;
  x = z*z;
}
</source>

